1
00:00:10,267 --> 00:00:11,133
<i>- You, monster!
- Monster!</i>

2
00:00:11,267 --> 00:00:13,200
<i>- Stop it!
- Get out of my house!</i>

3
00:00:13,333 --> 00:00:15,200
<i>I will never kneel
to you, Hazel.</i>

4
00:00:15,733 --> 00:00:17,233
<i> I kneel only before God!</i>

5
00:00:17,367 --> 00:00:18,467
<i> Then keep denying,</i>

6
00:00:18,600 --> 00:00:21,067
<i>even if Timo's testimony already
slapped you in the face!</i>

7
00:00:21,200 --> 00:00:22,600
<i> Go on, say it.</i>

8
00:00:22,733 --> 00:00:24,600
<i> Swear on your daughter</i>

9
00:00:24,733 --> 00:00:26,433
<i> that you didn't pay Timo.</i>

10
00:00:27,567 --> 00:00:28,967
<i>What is it, Mom?
Did you get anything from her?</i>

11
00:00:29,100 --> 00:00:30,133
<i> Nothing, right?</i>

12
00:00:30,267 --> 00:00:34,033
<i>Even if she didn't say it
outright, I caught her.</i>

13
00:00:34,200 --> 00:00:37,333
<i>Mom, silence doesn't
always mean yes.</i>

14
00:00:37,467 --> 00:00:39,667
<i>But a mother's instinct is real.</i>

15
00:00:39,800 --> 00:00:40,867
<i> Mom, I'm sorry, okay?</i>

16
00:00:41,000 --> 00:00:44,167
<i>But if I have to,
I'll destroy Jessica's image.</i>

17
00:00:44,300 --> 00:00:46,667
<i>Maybe we should do
what Jeffrey suggested.</i>

18
00:00:46,800 --> 00:00:48,133
<i> Destroy Jessica's image?</i>

19
00:00:48,267 --> 00:00:51,067
<i>- Manuel, no.
- No, not Jessica.</i>

20
00:00:51,200 --> 00:00:55,033
<i>Timo. We'll find someone
we can ask to do that.</i>

21
00:00:55,167 --> 00:00:59,033
<i>Atty. Yeban said, everyone
he talked to about Timo</i>

22
00:00:59,167 --> 00:01:00,600
<i>had nothing but good things
to say.</i>

23
00:01:00,733 --> 00:01:02,867
<i>So I hired
a private investigator</i>

24
00:01:03,000 --> 00:01:04,600
<i>to dig up the dirt on his life.</i>

25
00:01:04,733 --> 00:01:07,067
<i>If we want to ruin
his credibility,</i>

26
00:01:07,200 --> 00:01:08,767
<i> we need evidence.</i>

27
00:01:13,267 --> 00:01:16,000
Felma, Manuel, by the way...

28
00:01:16,133 --> 00:01:17,733
Has Atty. Yeban told you that

29
00:01:17,867 --> 00:01:20,400
we're being moved
to another court?

30
00:01:20,967 --> 00:01:22,133
What?

31
00:01:23,967 --> 00:01:25,533
No, he hasn't.

32
00:01:25,667 --> 00:01:27,900
Oh, why?

33
00:01:28,033 --> 00:01:31,600
The Judge found out that

34
00:01:31,733 --> 00:01:33,900
Timo's mother-in-law
is his distant relative.

35
00:01:34,033 --> 00:01:35,600
So he voluntarily inhibits.

36
00:01:36,567 --> 00:01:37,933
You know what we should do?

37
00:01:43,433 --> 00:01:45,233
<i> We will show the court</i>

38
00:01:45,467 --> 00:01:47,233
<i>what kind of person
Coleen is.</i>

39
00:01:47,367 --> 00:01:50,367
<i>We'll show them that she's
incapable of killing anyone.</i>

40
00:01:50,500 --> 00:01:53,533
Honestly, Your Honor,
before everything happened...

41
00:01:54,567 --> 00:01:56,367
they were so close
to each other.

42
00:01:57,200 --> 00:02:01,267
<i>Jessica was the one who brought
dad and Coleen together.</i>

43
00:02:02,100 --> 00:02:03,900
The truth is...

44
00:02:04,033 --> 00:02:04,900
Jeffrey and I were the ones

45
00:02:05,033 --> 00:02:07,700
who were mad at dad
and Jessica at first.

46
00:02:09,767 --> 00:02:10,833
But Coleen...

47
00:02:12,633 --> 00:02:17,667
<i>Coleen defended Jessica
and dad from us.</i>

48
00:02:17,833 --> 00:02:19,133
She was even the one
who organized

49
00:02:19,267 --> 00:02:21,533
Jessica's 18th birthday party.

50
00:02:24,233 --> 00:02:26,567
I helped Felma raise Coleen.

51
00:02:29,500 --> 00:02:31,333
She's like my daughter,
your Honor.

52
00:02:32,867 --> 00:02:34,433
That's why I know her very well.

53
00:02:36,500 --> 00:02:40,667
And she's not someone
who would wish harm on anyone.

54
00:02:42,000 --> 00:02:43,833
Felma didn't raise her
to be like that.

55
00:02:47,300 --> 00:02:49,067
I didn't raise her
to be like that.

56
00:02:51,000 --> 00:02:52,133
Your Honor...

57
00:02:55,167 --> 00:02:56,333
I have to admit that...

58
00:02:57,700 --> 00:02:59,000
<i> Coleen is not perfect.</i>

59
00:03:00,033 --> 00:03:01,233
<i> She has her flaws.</i>

60
00:03:02,900 --> 00:03:05,867
Sometimes, she's stubborn.

61
00:03:09,333 --> 00:03:10,567
<i> She doesn't obey.</i>

62
00:03:11,800 --> 00:03:13,233
<i> A typical youngest child.</i>

63
00:03:14,267 --> 00:03:15,667
<i>But besides her imperfection...</i>

64
00:03:16,967 --> 00:03:18,700
she is not capable of murder.

65
00:03:19,767 --> 00:03:20,667
She's not.

66
00:03:21,500 --> 00:03:23,833
And she will never be capable
of harming others.

67
00:03:32,833 --> 00:03:37,500
Miss Felma Ruiz,
the defense has painted

68
00:03:37,633 --> 00:03:42,533
that your daughter is kind
and incapable of harm.

69
00:03:43,933 --> 00:03:46,000
But let's address the issue.

70
00:03:47,933 --> 00:03:51,033
Didn't Jessica and Coleen
have multiple arguments

71
00:03:51,167 --> 00:03:52,567
before the incident happened?

72
00:03:56,700 --> 00:03:57,600
That's true.

73
00:03:59,433 --> 00:04:01,667
They had misunderstandings.

74
00:04:02,733 --> 00:04:05,633
<i>- Just like any other siblings.
- Stop it!</i>

75
00:04:06,800 --> 00:04:11,433
<i>Petty fights, hurt feelings,
and jealousy.</i>

76
00:04:12,533 --> 00:04:13,900
So there was jealousy?

77
00:04:21,133 --> 00:04:21,767
Yes.

78
00:04:23,900 --> 00:04:26,800
For their father's love
and attention.

79
00:04:30,267 --> 00:04:31,900
But we tried...

80
00:04:33,800 --> 00:04:35,367
to make them reconcile.

81
00:04:36,667 --> 00:04:41,467
But like any ordinary teenagers,
we couldn't force them.

82
00:04:42,600 --> 00:04:45,000
<i>So we let them
work things out...</i>

83
00:04:46,000 --> 00:04:47,533
and make up on their own.

84
00:04:52,433 --> 00:04:57,533
Didn't Jessica ever feel
her life was in danger?

85
00:04:57,667 --> 00:04:59,300
Objection, Your Honor.

86
00:05:00,400 --> 00:05:01,400
Incompetent.

87
00:05:01,533 --> 00:05:03,800
The witness
cannot possibly testify

88
00:05:03,933 --> 00:05:05,200
to the victim's state of mind.

89
00:05:08,767 --> 00:05:09,833
Sustained.

90
00:05:09,967 --> 00:05:13,300
Rephrase your question, Counsel.

91
00:05:19,167 --> 00:05:24,033
So, after all the tension
between the two girls,

92
00:05:26,267 --> 00:05:28,033
you just let them make up
on their own?

93
00:05:29,467 --> 00:05:33,900
Like I said,
we didn't force them.

94
00:05:34,667 --> 00:05:37,433
But we often reminded them

95
00:05:37,567 --> 00:05:39,967
to fix the problem
because they're siblings.

96
00:05:40,833 --> 00:05:42,900
I always tell Coleen...

97
00:05:43,867 --> 00:05:46,100
<i> and let Jessica feel that...</i>

98
00:05:48,233 --> 00:05:49,567
<i> we're a family.</i>

99
00:05:50,600 --> 00:05:54,333
Jessica had been a part
of our family.

100
00:05:57,767 --> 00:06:02,000
That's why,
after Manuel, Jeffrey,

101
00:06:02,133 --> 00:06:03,567
and Andrea reconciled...

102
00:06:04,400 --> 00:06:08,167
they may not have openly sided

103
00:06:08,333 --> 00:06:09,967
of their older siblings,
with Jessica,

104
00:06:10,100 --> 00:06:14,767
but they always reminded
Coleen...

105
00:06:15,867 --> 00:06:19,100
to stay humble, understand...

106
00:06:20,167 --> 00:06:23,933
and act like the big sister
to their youngest sibling.

107
00:06:33,433 --> 00:06:37,667
Your Honor, Coleen and Jessica
are both my daughters.

108
00:06:39,467 --> 00:06:40,933
I love them both.

109
00:06:42,267 --> 00:06:44,367
<i> I'm not taking any side.</i>

110
00:06:46,000 --> 00:06:48,433
<i>I recently reconciled
with my children.</i>

111
00:06:49,633 --> 00:06:54,800
<i>I was sure that Coleen and
Jessica would reconcile, too.</i>

112
00:06:56,300 --> 00:06:59,033
You heard her statement.

113
00:07:00,133 --> 00:07:04,333
Before the accident happened,

114
00:07:04,467 --> 00:07:07,867
Coleen really wanted to make
peace with her sister.

115
00:07:09,267 --> 00:07:10,900
So there's no reason for her

116
00:07:11,033 --> 00:07:14,033
to do something bad
or harm Jessica.

117
00:07:14,200 --> 00:07:15,100
There's nothing.

118
00:07:15,233 --> 00:07:16,433
Oh, come on, Manuel!

119
00:07:17,133 --> 00:07:19,567
Quit trying to clean up
Coleen's name!

120
00:07:19,700 --> 00:07:20,767
She pushed Jessica!

121
00:07:20,900 --> 00:07:21,767
She killed our daughter!

122
00:07:21,900 --> 00:07:23,167
Don't you understand that?

123
00:07:23,300 --> 00:07:24,833
Hazel, stop it!

124
00:07:24,967 --> 00:07:25,933
It's true!

125
00:07:26,067 --> 00:07:27,267
<i>- Order in the court!
- You keep saying</i>

126
00:07:27,400 --> 00:07:28,367
nonsense things, Manuel!

127
00:07:28,500 --> 00:07:30,833
<i> Order in the court!</i>

128
00:07:36,467 --> 00:07:37,500
<i> Miss Hazel Cruz,</i>

129
00:07:37,633 --> 00:07:40,100
can you tell the Honorable Court
about the relationship

130
00:07:40,233 --> 00:07:42,400
of your daughter Jessica
and Coleen?

131
00:07:43,933 --> 00:07:45,867
Jessica was always crying to me

132
00:07:47,400 --> 00:07:51,033
because Coleen was bullying her.

133
00:07:54,300 --> 00:07:57,867
That's why I can't accept
what the defense said

134
00:07:58,000 --> 00:07:59,100
in the last hearing.

135
00:08:01,467 --> 00:08:06,267
They're making it seem like
Coleen is such a good person.

136
00:08:07,133 --> 00:08:08,867
hat's not true, Your Honor.

137
00:08:10,833 --> 00:08:12,167
You mentioned bullying.

138
00:08:13,233 --> 00:08:15,433
How was Jessica bullied
by the accused?

139
00:08:18,633 --> 00:08:20,800
Coleen was hurting Jessica.

140
00:08:22,033 --> 00:08:25,567
I saw Jessica's bruises...

141
00:08:28,600 --> 00:08:30,800
and wounds on her arms.

142
00:08:32,100 --> 00:08:33,333
<i> And she said...</i>

143
00:08:34,433 --> 00:08:36,467
she was scared for her life.

144
00:08:38,167 --> 00:08:40,100
No further questions,
Your Honor.

145
00:08:42,333 --> 00:08:43,900
Mrs. Cruz,

146
00:08:44,033 --> 00:08:50,500
you mentioned Jessica was hurt
because of Coleen's bullying.

147
00:08:52,000 --> 00:08:52,867
Yet...

148
00:08:53,733 --> 00:09:00,800
you don't have any proof
of the wounds

149
00:09:00,967 --> 00:09:03,467
and bruises
you mentioned earlier.

150
00:09:04,533 --> 00:09:07,300
That would make
that claim true, right?

151
00:09:08,600 --> 00:09:09,333
Yes.

152
00:09:10,633 --> 00:09:11,867
You also said, Mrs. Cruz,

153
00:09:12,000 --> 00:09:14,967
that Jessica always cried
to you.

154
00:09:15,700 --> 00:09:20,567
Could it be that
she cried to you

155
00:09:20,700 --> 00:09:21,833
not because of Coleen,

156
00:09:21,967 --> 00:09:25,767
but because,
as Mr. Manuel Cruz stated,

157
00:09:26,967 --> 00:09:29,200
he and Jessica abandoned you

158
00:09:29,367 --> 00:09:32,000
after repeated instances
of abuse?

159
00:09:32,133 --> 00:09:33,667
- Objection!
- Excuse me?

160
00:09:33,800 --> 00:09:34,733
What kind of a question is that?

161
00:09:35,000 --> 00:09:36,767
I'm not the one on trial here.

162
00:09:36,900 --> 00:09:38,867
Your Honor, I'm just trying

163
00:09:39,000 --> 00:09:42,533
to establish the nature
of her relationship

164
00:09:42,667 --> 00:09:43,833
with her daughter.

165
00:09:43,967 --> 00:09:48,867
So that the court can determine
if her statements are credible.

166
00:09:49,000 --> 00:09:50,233
Irrelevant, Your Honor!

167
00:09:51,200 --> 00:09:52,567
Objection, sustained.

168
00:09:53,267 --> 00:09:54,500
Counsel is reminded

169
00:09:54,633 --> 00:09:57,133
to please confine
this questions on matters

170
00:09:57,267 --> 00:09:58,467
material to this case.

171
00:10:01,533 --> 00:10:02,733
We submit, Your Honor.

172
00:10:07,900 --> 00:10:09,467
Mrs. Cruz, you said...

173
00:10:10,967 --> 00:10:13,467
that Jessica was scared
for her life.

174
00:10:14,400 --> 00:10:19,100
Did she say it was because
Coleen was threatening her?

175
00:10:21,867 --> 00:10:22,600
Yes.

176
00:10:23,167 --> 00:10:24,000
If so...

177
00:10:25,167 --> 00:10:29,300
when and where did this alleged
threat transpire?

178
00:10:30,833 --> 00:10:36,200
The day the chaos
broke out at FMP...

179
00:10:37,433 --> 00:10:40,400
because of Coleen's sister,
Andrea's scamming.

180
00:10:41,833 --> 00:10:46,133
Before that,
Jessica came to me...

181
00:10:48,467 --> 00:10:50,833
<i> at the condo I was renting.</i>

182
00:10:50,967 --> 00:10:55,733
<i>And I saw that,
it covered with bruises...</i>

183
00:10:58,167 --> 00:10:59,433
and wounds...

184
00:11:01,300 --> 00:11:02,767
on her arms.

185
00:11:05,333 --> 00:11:06,867
That was when I found out...

186
00:11:08,133 --> 00:11:10,167
Coleen was hurting her.

187
00:11:12,567 --> 00:11:14,867
And she was scared for her life.

188
00:11:15,000 --> 00:11:20,333
Do you have any proof
to back up your claim?

189
00:11:21,700 --> 00:11:26,833
Perhaps a recording or witness
that can confirm it.

190
00:11:38,367 --> 00:11:41,300
Please answer truthfully,
Mrs. Cruz.

191
00:11:41,467 --> 00:11:43,900
May I remind you
that you are under oath.

192
00:11:46,833 --> 00:11:47,800
I have none.

193
00:11:50,733 --> 00:11:53,067
It was just my daughter
and me talking.

194
00:11:53,200 --> 00:11:55,133
No further questions,
Your Honor.

195
00:12:07,367 --> 00:12:09,533
Hazel, friend.

196
00:12:09,800 --> 00:12:12,000
Please talk to me.

197
00:12:12,300 --> 00:12:13,667
Friend.

198
00:12:13,800 --> 00:12:16,200
After you abandoned me in court?

199
00:12:16,467 --> 00:12:18,333
I didn't abandon you.

200
00:12:18,467 --> 00:12:20,433
I was just worried
you'd mention me.

201
00:12:20,567 --> 00:12:23,167
I didn't hear your conversation
with my godchild.

202
00:12:23,533 --> 00:12:26,167
I might be called
to the witness stand,

203
00:12:26,400 --> 00:12:28,200
and what I say might not match.

204
00:12:29,700 --> 00:12:30,700
What now, Alice?

205
00:12:31,767 --> 00:12:35,633
Should I just let the court see
Coleen as a saint

206
00:12:35,767 --> 00:12:37,000
because of her kindness?

207
00:12:37,133 --> 00:12:40,067
Timo's statement is strong.

208
00:12:41,133 --> 00:12:43,633
But it will affect
the Judge's decision.

209
00:12:44,600 --> 00:12:46,300
What if he reduces the sentence?

210
00:12:47,500 --> 00:12:48,367
I won't let that happen.

211
00:12:49,600 --> 00:12:51,067
I have to do something.

212
00:12:53,267 --> 00:12:54,400
But...

213
00:12:55,433 --> 00:12:56,200
what is it?

214
00:12:57,733 --> 00:12:59,067
What do we do?

215
00:12:59,933 --> 00:13:02,100
I can't find anyone who has ever
had issues with Coleen

216
00:13:02,233 --> 00:13:05,033
to show that she isn't
as good as they claim.

217
00:13:08,867 --> 00:13:09,967
Sweetheart.

218
00:13:11,467 --> 00:13:14,500
Dad, thank you...

219
00:13:15,733 --> 00:13:17,533
for defending me.

220
00:13:18,300 --> 00:13:19,500
All of you.

221
00:13:21,033 --> 00:13:24,367
Dear, I just told the truth.

222
00:13:26,700 --> 00:13:29,533
I don't believe what Timo said.

223
00:13:31,700 --> 00:13:33,233
I'm already tired, Dad.

224
00:13:35,367 --> 00:13:37,533
I feel nervous every day.

225
00:13:39,267 --> 00:13:41,600
I'm scared that
I might go to jail.

226
00:13:42,367 --> 00:13:43,300
Dear...

227
00:13:44,600 --> 00:13:47,433
we won't let that happen.

228
00:13:48,600 --> 00:13:50,433
But how, Dad?

229
00:13:51,767 --> 00:13:54,967
Nobody's disputing
Timo's statement.

230
00:13:56,733 --> 00:13:58,467
I don't know why he insists

231
00:13:58,600 --> 00:14:01,733
that I pushed Jessica
even if I didn't.

232
00:14:01,867 --> 00:14:03,133
For what?

233
00:14:03,967 --> 00:14:05,967
So that his sentence
can be reduced?

234
00:14:06,867 --> 00:14:08,300
I don't know either, Dear.

235
00:14:09,133 --> 00:14:10,833
But your mom and I suspect...

236
00:14:12,533 --> 00:14:14,467
that Hazel paid Timo.

237
00:14:15,500 --> 00:14:17,567
Hazel is so evil, Dad.

238
00:14:18,567 --> 00:14:21,100
She just really wants me
in jail.

239
00:14:21,233 --> 00:14:24,900
Dear, I won't let that happen.

240
00:14:25,033 --> 00:14:26,667
There's nothing
I wouldn't do for you.

241
00:14:26,800 --> 00:14:27,933
I promise.

242
00:14:28,100 --> 00:14:29,667
I'll do everything for you.

243
00:14:29,800 --> 00:14:31,333
Even if it costs me my life.

244
00:14:42,533 --> 00:14:44,433
Do we stand
a strong chance, Attorney?

245
00:14:47,567 --> 00:14:50,667
Well, I really can't tell.

246
00:14:50,800 --> 00:14:53,333
Yes, we proved
to the court that...

247
00:14:54,433 --> 00:14:55,800
Coleen is a good person.

248
00:14:55,933 --> 00:15:00,167
But Timo's testimony
remains solid.

249
00:15:00,300 --> 00:15:02,533
The Judge might still
lean on it.

250
00:15:02,700 --> 00:15:04,633
Since no one's disputing it.

251
00:15:06,800 --> 00:15:08,533
Mom? Dad?

252
00:15:08,667 --> 00:15:10,433
- Sweetheart.
- I don't want to go to jail.

253
00:15:10,567 --> 00:15:11,600
- Coleen?
- Coleen?

254
00:15:11,733 --> 00:15:12,933
- I don't want to, Mom.
- Dear.

255
00:15:13,067 --> 00:15:14,633
Dear.

256
00:15:22,933 --> 00:15:25,167
Coleen, dear, relax.

257
00:15:26,167 --> 00:15:28,833
I'm talking to the private
investigator that I hired.

258
00:15:29,733 --> 00:15:34,133
He won't stop
until he finds evidence

259
00:15:34,300 --> 00:15:37,567
to challenge Timo's credibility.

260
00:15:38,633 --> 00:15:39,400
Dear...

261
00:15:40,533 --> 00:15:42,467
our fight isn't over yet.

262
00:15:53,067 --> 00:15:56,367
Attorney, I have a favor to ask.

263
00:15:56,500 --> 00:15:58,700
I have to meet Timo Malabanan.

264
00:16:08,200 --> 00:16:09,433
I'm begging you.

265
00:16:10,233 --> 00:16:11,533
Retract your statement.

266
00:16:11,667 --> 00:16:13,267
Speak the truth now.

267
00:16:15,667 --> 00:16:17,400
I already told the truth, Sir.

268
00:16:17,533 --> 00:16:18,533
No, you're not.

269
00:16:19,300 --> 00:16:20,567
You're lying.

270
00:16:21,233 --> 00:16:22,900
Why would I lie?

271
00:16:24,200 --> 00:16:25,967
Sir, I'm a decent person.

272
00:16:27,533 --> 00:16:30,000
I didn't mean
what happened to Jessica.

273
00:16:30,933 --> 00:16:33,600
I turned myself in
to pay for what I did.

274
00:16:34,633 --> 00:16:36,100
I have kids, too.

275
00:16:36,900 --> 00:16:38,300
I don't want them thinking

276
00:16:38,433 --> 00:16:40,633
it's okay to flee
from their sins.

277
00:16:42,033 --> 00:16:43,367
Or lie.

278
00:16:44,200 --> 00:16:46,800
We should always tell the truth.

279
00:16:47,367 --> 00:16:49,200
Are you telling the truth?

280
00:16:49,333 --> 00:16:51,967
- Or did Hazel tell you...
- That Ma'am Hazel paid me off?

281
00:16:53,100 --> 00:16:55,900
You're no different from
your other wife, Miss Felma.

282
00:16:56,800 --> 00:16:59,500
Why do you insist
that I was paid?

283
00:17:00,267 --> 00:17:02,300
Because Coleen
didn't push Jessica!

284
00:17:03,000 --> 00:17:04,200
And you know that!

285
00:17:06,667 --> 00:17:08,333
I thought you said
you were a decent man?

286
00:17:08,633 --> 00:17:10,333
You were a good father?

287
00:17:11,267 --> 00:17:14,067
Can you really put
an innocent child in jail?

288
00:17:15,600 --> 00:17:16,700
I'm sorry, Sir.

289
00:17:17,200 --> 00:17:20,433
But I can't retract
my statement.

290
00:17:21,267 --> 00:17:24,067
I saw Coleen push Jessica.

291
00:17:24,200 --> 00:17:25,400
That's why I hit her.

292
00:17:39,267 --> 00:17:40,367
Dad.

293
00:17:40,733 --> 00:17:42,400
How did your meeting
with Timo go?

294
00:17:44,433 --> 00:17:45,867
<i> Sir, I'm a decent person.</i>

295
00:17:46,000 --> 00:17:48,867
<i>I turned myself in
to pay for what I did.</i>

296
00:17:57,067 --> 00:17:58,067
That's enough, stop it.

297
00:17:58,200 --> 00:17:59,400
Don't hurt yourself, Dad.

298
00:17:59,533 --> 00:18:00,467
That's enough.

299
00:18:09,367 --> 00:18:10,867
Manuel was here earlier?

300
00:18:14,200 --> 00:18:16,233
But don't worry, Ma'am.

301
00:18:16,367 --> 00:18:17,700
I didn't fold.

302
00:18:18,267 --> 00:18:19,400
I didn't throw you
under the bus.

303
00:18:20,233 --> 00:18:23,067
But, Ma'am, I admit...

304
00:18:23,233 --> 00:18:25,833
I feel guilty about
what I told your husband.

305
00:18:28,333 --> 00:18:30,867
I saw the pain in his eyes.

306
00:18:31,900 --> 00:18:33,100
Oh, please.

307
00:18:33,233 --> 00:18:36,033
Don't even consider
my husband's feelings.

308
00:18:36,167 --> 00:18:37,500
How can I do that?

309
00:18:37,633 --> 00:18:39,667
We're both fathers.

310
00:18:39,800 --> 00:18:40,900
I killed her daughter,

311
00:18:41,033 --> 00:18:43,967
and the other one will go
to jail also because of me.

312
00:18:45,133 --> 00:18:46,600
What are you trying to say?

313
00:18:47,733 --> 00:18:49,067
Are you really feeling guilty
after everything?

314
00:18:50,267 --> 00:18:53,400
Just think about your family.

315
00:18:53,533 --> 00:18:55,967
You're doing this for them.

316
00:18:57,333 --> 00:19:01,933
You don't want me to stop
supporting them, right?

317
00:19:04,033 --> 00:19:07,367
Remember, next month...

318
00:19:08,400 --> 00:19:10,333
Diana is giving birth, right?

319
00:19:11,533 --> 00:19:15,367
And I heard she's having
a C-section

320
00:19:15,500 --> 00:19:16,833
because the baby's
in a breech position.

321
00:19:16,967 --> 00:19:18,133
Oh, dear.

322
00:19:19,633 --> 00:19:21,467
That means...

323
00:19:21,600 --> 00:19:23,933
she'll be needing
a huge amount of money.

324
00:19:32,067 --> 00:19:34,133
My private investigator
discovered something

325
00:19:34,267 --> 00:19:35,200
about Timo.

326
00:19:35,333 --> 00:19:36,367
Look, Felma.

327
00:19:41,433 --> 00:19:43,800
He worked for two years
as a driver

328
00:19:43,933 --> 00:19:46,433
for Councilor Parse
of the First District.

329
00:19:47,500 --> 00:19:50,400
And he suddenly got fired.

330
00:19:51,967 --> 00:19:55,133
He had a fight
with his employer.

331
00:19:56,467 --> 00:19:58,000
Violence!

332
00:20:00,133 --> 00:20:02,333
With Councilor Parse himself?

333
00:20:02,500 --> 00:20:03,133
Yes.

334
00:20:05,533 --> 00:20:06,533
You know what, Felma?

335
00:20:07,933 --> 00:20:13,767
This might help our plan
to discredit Timo.

336
00:20:14,867 --> 00:20:16,700
I'll find out the reason.

337
00:20:16,833 --> 00:20:19,500
Councilor Parse
isn't here right now.

338
00:20:19,633 --> 00:20:20,900
He's in Zamboanga.

339
00:20:21,033 --> 00:20:23,433
But I'll go to him
once he returns

340
00:20:23,567 --> 00:20:25,467
and I'll talk to him myself.

341
00:20:28,400 --> 00:20:29,600
Thank you, Noah.

342
00:20:30,967 --> 00:20:32,433
It's nothing, Felma.

343
00:20:36,233 --> 00:20:37,867
Oh, Manuel.

344
00:20:38,000 --> 00:20:40,733
Noah has good news.

345
00:20:40,867 --> 00:20:42,467
Yes, I heard.

346
00:20:42,600 --> 00:20:44,933
He's the hero again
and you're very pleased.

347
00:20:45,067 --> 00:20:46,067
Manuel!

348
00:20:50,900 --> 00:20:52,000
Bro, what's your problem?

349
00:20:52,133 --> 00:20:53,267
You are the problem!

350
00:20:53,767 --> 00:20:55,800
You're overstepping
in my family!

351
00:20:56,500 --> 00:20:57,733
I'm helping,

352
00:20:58,233 --> 00:20:59,400
not overstepping.

353
00:21:00,733 --> 00:21:01,667
Are you helping,

354
00:21:01,800 --> 00:21:02,600
or are you trying to make
yourself look good?

355
00:21:03,800 --> 00:21:05,467
You're not part of my family.

356
00:21:06,100 --> 00:21:07,933
Let us resolve our problem
on our own!

357
00:21:08,800 --> 00:21:09,967
You know what your problem is?

358
00:21:10,533 --> 00:21:12,767
You're putting a sinister spin
on my help.

359
00:21:12,900 --> 00:21:16,300
Felma, looks like
my help isn't needed.

360
00:21:16,533 --> 00:21:18,567
Fine, I'm out.

361
00:21:23,900 --> 00:21:25,033
Really, Manuel?

362
00:21:25,733 --> 00:21:27,300
You're letting your pride
get in the way?

363
00:21:28,900 --> 00:21:30,067
Now, really?

364
00:21:31,133 --> 00:21:33,500
When your child could end up
in jail?

365
00:21:35,000 --> 00:21:36,033
Yes, Dad.

366
00:21:37,233 --> 00:21:38,467
We need help.

367
00:21:39,067 --> 00:21:42,533
And Uncle Noah
isn't a stranger to us.

368
00:21:44,933 --> 00:21:46,033
Sorry, Felma.

369
00:21:46,633 --> 00:21:48,367
I didn't mean it.

370
00:21:59,467 --> 00:22:00,967
Thank you so much...

371
00:22:01,400 --> 00:22:02,767
for visiting me in my dream.

372
00:22:02,900 --> 00:22:06,567
But you were crying
and telling me to forgive you

373
00:22:06,700 --> 00:22:07,567
and your mom.

374
00:22:07,700 --> 00:22:08,767
And to take care of her.

375
00:22:08,900 --> 00:22:10,667
She visits me in my dreams
every night.

376
00:22:10,800 --> 00:22:13,333
She's telling me
everything will be fine.

377
00:22:13,467 --> 00:22:16,333
She wants you to forgive me
and take care of me.

378
00:22:16,500 --> 00:22:18,033
Is that what you dream, too?

379
00:22:18,167 --> 00:22:19,067
Yes, Manuel.

380
00:22:19,200 --> 00:22:21,167
Does Jessica visit you
in your dreams, too?

381
00:22:21,300 --> 00:22:23,067
Did she also tell you
her last wish?

382
00:22:23,200 --> 00:22:25,067
She wants us
to get back together.

383
00:22:25,200 --> 00:22:26,533
Are you Diana Malabanan?

384
00:22:26,667 --> 00:22:27,567
Yes, it's me.

385
00:22:27,700 --> 00:22:28,600
Who are you?

386
00:22:28,733 --> 00:22:31,233
I'm Hazel,
Jessica Cruz's mother.

387
00:22:31,367 --> 00:22:33,700
The child that your husband,
Timo, ran over and killed.

388
00:22:33,833 --> 00:22:35,900
Ma'am, please have mercy
on my baby.

389
00:22:36,033 --> 00:22:37,367
He turned himself in already.

390
00:22:37,500 --> 00:22:39,400
What else do you want him to do?

391
00:22:39,533 --> 00:22:42,767
You keep your mouth shut
whenever you find something out.

392
00:22:42,900 --> 00:22:43,967
Because if you don't,

393
00:22:44,100 --> 00:22:47,833
something bad will happen
to Timo in jail.

394
00:22:47,967 --> 00:22:49,867
What did your PI say, Noah?

395
00:22:50,033 --> 00:22:51,400
He's an upright person.

396
00:22:51,533 --> 00:22:53,767
Someone with strong convictions
and principles.

397
00:22:53,900 --> 00:22:56,400
That's why breaking
his credibility will be tough.

398
00:22:56,533 --> 00:22:58,567
Are we likely to lose?

399
00:22:58,700 --> 00:22:59,667
Coleen can't go to jail.

400
00:22:59,800 --> 00:23:01,033
She can't be jailed.

401
00:23:01,167 --> 00:23:02,400
Mom, she's too young.

402
00:23:02,533 --> 00:23:05,533
If Hazel paid Timo
to ruin Coleen,

403
00:23:05,667 --> 00:23:08,833
I'll pay him
to take it all back.

404
00:23:08,967 --> 00:23:12,033
I can double or triple
what Hazel gave him.
